I"<p>Adolescence is characterized by seeking novelty and <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/contrastive-learning-is-deviant-based-norm-setting">avoiding norms</a>. This hints towards a biologically-implemented mechanism which maximizes reward in an early-stopping setting on <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/internalizing-beliefs-incurs-ideological-debt">an ideological level</a>, analogous to mating patterns in many species. In this view, adolescence is an exacerbated phase of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/psychological-foraging-resembles-simulated-annealing">cognitive and behavioral foraging</a>.</p>
